{"type":"message","id":"65afc5d9","parentId":"5089c23a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:54:17.146Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4ri0l3msk026_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-23 185347\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and decide on a concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nThe current pending task is implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The next action is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLooking at the file structure mentioned:\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` - pulse logs\r\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` - already exists with the hypothesis\r\n\r\nI should implement a TIC classifier. Let me create a script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariants (patterns that persist across pulses) vs variants (session-specific content)\r\n3. Measures classification accuracy\r\n4. Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me first check what's in the logs directory and the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md to understand the current state better.\r\n\r\nActually, I should just pick ONE concrete action. The most immediate next step would be to create a TIC experiment script that can analyze the pulse logs and classify invariant vs variant content.\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier to identify invariant (persistent) vs variant (session-specific) content across pulse logs. I need to create the experimental framework first.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that reads pulse logs, extracts patterns, classifies content as invariant or variant, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MinInvariantOccurrence = 3,\r\n    [float]$InvariantThreshold = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$ProjectRoot = Split-Path -Parent $PSScriptRoot\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$LogDir = Join-Path $ProjectRoot \"logs\"\r\n$Logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($Logs.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\nif ($Logs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Warning \"Need at least 5 logs for meaningful analysis\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract patterns from each log\r\nfunction Extract-Patterns {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $patterns = @{\r\n        References = @()  # @mentions, file paths, URLs\r\n        Actions = @()      # ACTION keywords, file edits\r\n        Observations = @() # OBSERVATION keywords, insights\r\n        Concepts = @()     # Key terms/phrases\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract references (file paths, @mentions)\r\n    $refPattern = '`([^`]+)`|@[\\w]+|[\\w\\/\\.-]+\\.(md|ps1|txt|csv)'\r\n    $patterns.References = [regex]::Matches($Content, $refPattern) | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract actions\r\n    $actionPattern = '(?i)(action|implement|create|edit|modify|update|must|need to)'\r\n    $patterns.Actions = [regex]::Matches($Content, $actionPattern) | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract observations (insights)\r\n    $obsPattern = '(?i)(insight|key finding|observation|realize|discover)'\r\n    $patterns.Observations = [regex]::Matches($Content, $obsPattern) | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key concepts (capitalized multi-word phrases)\r\n    $conceptPattern = '\\b[A-Z][a-z]+(?:\\s+[A-Z][a-z]+)+\\b'\r\n    $patterns.Concepts = [regex]::Matches($Content, $conceptPattern) | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    \r\n    return $patterns\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Analyze each log\r\n$LogData = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $Logs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $patterns = Extract-Patterns -Content $content\r\n    \r\n    $LogData += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Name = $log.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Patterns = $patterns\r\n        Timestamp = $log.BaseName -replace 'pulse_', ''\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify invariants (patterns appearing in >= MinInvariantOccurrence logs)\r\n$AllPatterns = @{\r\n    References = @{}\r\n    Actions = @{}\r\n    Observations = @{}\r\n    Concepts = @{}\r\n}\r\n\r\nforeach ($data in $LogData) {\r\n    foreach ($type in @('References', 'Actions', 'Observations', 'Concepts')) {\r\n        foreach ($pattern in $data.Patterns.$type) {\r\n            $key = $pattern.ToLower()\r\n            if (-not $AllPatterns.$type.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n                $AllPatterns.$type[$key] = 0\r\n            }\r\n            $AllPatterns.$type[$key]++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify as invariant or variant\r\n$InvariantPatterns = @{}\r\n$VariantPatterns = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($type in @('References', 'Actions', 'Observations', 'Concepts')) {\r\n    $InvariantPatterns[$type] = @()\r\n    $VariantPatterns[$type] = @()\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($kv in $AllPatterns.$type.GetEnumerator()) {\r\n        $ratio = $kv.Value / $Logs.Count\r\n        if ($ratio -ge $InvariantThreshold) {\r\n            $InvariantPatterns[$type\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 18:54:11\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774306457143}}
