{"type":"message","id":"46060e07","parentId":"a8178bdb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:54:20.556Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x7dtsobhvmlm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿experiments/tic_classifier.ps1\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\n\nparam(\n    [int]$MinInvariantOccurrence = 3,\n    [float]$InvariantThreshold = 0.7\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n$ProjectRoot = Split-Path -Parent $PSScriptRoot\n\n# Load pulse logs\n$LogDir = Join-Path $ProjectRoot \"logs\"\n$Logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\n\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\nWrite-Host \"Found $($Logs.Count) pulse logs\"\n\nif ($Logs.Count -lt 5) {\n    Write-Warning \"Need at least 5 logs for meaningful analysis\"\n    exit 1\n}\n\n# Extract patterns from each log\nfunction Extract-Patterns {\n    param([string]$Content)\n    \n    $patterns = @{\n        References = @()  # @mentions, file paths, URLs\n        Actions = @()      # ACTION keywords, file edits\n        Observations = @() # OBSERVATION keywords, insights\n        Concepts = @()     # Key terms/phrases\n    }\n    \n    # Extract references (file paths, @mentions)\n    $refPattern = '`([^`]+)`|@[\\w]+|[\\w\\/\\.-]+\\.(md|ps1|txt|csv)'\n    $patterns.References = [regex]::Matches($Content, $refPattern) | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\n    \n    # Extract actions\n    $actionPattern = '(?i)(action|implement|create|edit|modify|update|must|need to)'\n    $patterns.Actions = [regex]::Matches($Content, $actionPattern) | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\n    \n    # Extract observations (insights)\n    $obsPattern = '(?i)(insight|key finding|observation|realize|discover)'\n    $patterns.Observations = [regex]::Matches($Content, $obsPattern) | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\n    \n    # Extract key concepts (capitalized multi-word phrases)\n    $conceptPattern = '\\b[A-Z][a-z]+(?:\\s+[A-Z][a-z]+)+\\b'\n    $patterns.Concepts = [regex]::Matches($Content, $conceptPattern) | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\n    \n    return $patterns\n}\n\n# Analyze each log\n$LogData = @()\nforeach ($log in $Logs) {\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\n    $patterns = Extract-Patterns -Content $content\n    \n    $LogData += [PSCustomObject]@{\n        Name = $log.Name\n        Content = $content\n        Patterns = $patterns\n        Timestamp = $log.BaseName -replace 'pulse_', ''\n    }\n}\n\n# Identify invariants (patterns appearing in >= MinInvariantOccurrence logs)\n$AllPatterns = @{\n    References = @{}\n    Actions = @{}\n    Observations = @{}\n    Concepts = @{}\n}\n\nforeach ($data in $LogData) {\n    foreach ($type in @('References', 'Actions', 'Observations', 'Concepts')) {\n        foreach ($pattern in $data.Patterns.$type) {\n            $key = $pattern.ToLower()\n            if (-not $AllPatterns.$type.ContainsKey($key)) {\n                $AllPatterns.$type[$key] = 0\n            }\n            $AllPatterns.$type[$key]++\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n# Classify as invariant or variant\n$InvariantPatterns = @{}\n$VariantPatterns = @{}\n\nforeach ($type in @('References', 'Actions', 'Observations', 'Concepts')) {\n    $InvariantPatterns[$type] = @()\n    $VariantPatterns[$type] = @()\n    \n    foreach ($kv in $AllPatterns.$type.GetEnumerator()) {\n        $ratio = $kv.Value / $Logs.Count\n        if ($ratio -ge $InvariantThreshold) {\n            $InvariantPatterns[$type\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774306460554}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed4c2241","parentId":"46060e07","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:54:29.360Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The pulse created:\n1. A new TIC classifier script at `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1`\n2. A new proposed mutation file\n3. Committed the changes to git\n\nThe observation was about the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment, which needs to be implemented to identify invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs.\n\nThe mutation was creating `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1`.\n\nLet me summarize this pulse cycle concisely.","thinkingSignature":"2f9841547e2129adb1899940a6b132e3fdffeb8c04c61fbbd257acd7608dd10f"},{"type":"text","text":"**Pulse Cycle Summary — 2026-03-23 18:53**\n\n**What happened:** The sandbox ran its 10-minute pulse cycle. The LLM analyzed the codebase and identified the next key experiment: **TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression)** — a classifier that tests whether causal structure IS invariant structure.\n\n**Applied mutation:** Created `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1` — a PowerShell script that reads all pulse logs (`logs/pulse_*.md`), extracts patterns (references, actions, observations, concepts), classifies them as **invariant** (appearing across ≥70% of logs) vs **variant** (session-specific), and measures classification accuracy against success criteria.\n\n**Key insight driving this:** The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis — if compression and causal discovery are the same problem, then the patterns that compress best across sessions are the causal backbone.\n\n**Proposed mutation waiting:** 1 (the classifier script itself, pending review/commit)\n\n**Git commit:** `0bbd99a` — 7 files changed, +389/-137 lines (new pulse log + proposed mutation committed; previous proposed mutation moved to `rejected/`)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4385,"output":341,"cacheRead":11887,